<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-224-718  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 224 718.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  March 12 1990 v24 n11 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC ready to loosen shackles on ATandamp;T business services. (FederalCommunications Commission)(includes related article on the FCC'sprice caps regulation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Betts, Mitch.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission proposes streamlining ATandamp;T'stariff regulations due to the fierce competition between MCI Corp,US Sprint Communications Corp and ATandamp;T for large corporateaccounts.andP;  The proposal eliminates the price ceiling and pricefloor imposed on ATandamp;T's business services and decreases the timerequired to get regulatory clearance to offer a new service from45 days to one day.andP;  Partial regulation would continue forbusiness services such as private lines, WATS, Megacom andSoftware Defined Network, and for services offered outside theprice caps jurisdiction.andP;  ATandamp;T's competitors are expected toprotest some of the proposal's stipulations and there have beencomplaints about ATandamp;T continuing to enjoy certain technicaladvantages.andP;  One problem is the possibility of ATandamp;T engaging inpredatory pricing, however, it would mean risking anotheranti-trust suit.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (rules and regulations).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationTariffPricing PolicyCompetitionTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>